docs/reviews/implementation-plan/codex-review.json:1839:    "description": "Large portions of the Tracker epic have no implementation task: US-TRK-02 pause/resume/clone/restart, US-TRK-04 injection site rotation, US-TRK-06 outcome logging, US-TRK-07 correlation timeline, US-TRK-08 cycles, US-TRK-09 reminders, and US-TRK-05 AC-1/AC-2 batch logging review flow.",
docs/reviews/implementation-plan/codex-review.json:1853:    "description": "Offline dose queuing and sync replay are placed after Ordering, but the architecture identifies offline dose log queuing and sync replay as a critical path for Tracker and US-TRK-03/US-TRK-05.",
docs/reviews/implementation-plan/codex-review.json:1860:    "description": "The task cites US-TRK-01 and US-TRK-03 but only covers vial decrement and idempotency. It omits schedule generation, managed-user assignment, required-field validation, timestamped logging, explicit skip events, suggested site, offline behavior, and empty-inventory warning.",
docs/reviews/implementation-plan/codex-review.json:1861:    "suggestion": "Split into Protocol Creation/Edit, Daily Dose Logging, Skip Handling, Inventory Warning, and Offline Sync tasks, each mapped to the exact US-TRK-01 and US-TRK-03 ACs."
docs/reviews/implementation-plan/codex-review.json:1867:    "description": "US-REC-01 is only partially covered. The plan includes Decimal math and tests for AC-1/AC-2 but omits guardrail warnings and displaying the user's last logged dose. US-REC-02 vial inventory persistence is absent.",
docs/reviews/implementation-plan/codex-review.json:1874:    "description": "Ordering coverage is incomplete. US-ORD-02 inventory-aware suggestions, US-ORD-05 receive-and-add-to-inventory, and US-ORD-07 state machine/stale flagging are missing. US-ORD-03 also omits archived sent-message history, and US-ORD-06 omits create/edit catalog products linked to compounds.",
docs/reviews/implementation-plan/codex-review.json:1881:    "description": "Several Auth/Admin ACs are not planned: US-AUT-01 onboarding, US-AUT-03 secure httpOnly cookies with 30-day rolling expiry, US-AUT-04 single-use reset tokens and email-enumeration privacy, US-ADM-01 managed-user restricted dashboard, and US-ADM-03 deactivate/reset managed users.",
docs/reviews/implementation-plan/codex-review.json:1888:    "description": "The Reference task covers search/category filtering and citation links but does not explicitly cover US-REF-01 ACs for IUPAC name, mechanism, administration routes, low/typical/high dosing ranges, protocol context, or stacking notes.",
docs/reviews/implementation-plan/codex-review.json:1909:    "description": "This mixes managed-user administration and adherence analytics. It cites US-ADM-02 and US-ADM-03 but only defines adherence output, leaving deactivation/reset behavior underspecified.",
