docs/reviews/user-stories/codex-review.json:1617:    "description": "US-TRK-01 uses '250mcg twice daily', but the PRD protocol frequency model only lists daily, EOD, specific days of week, and custom day intervals. Twice-daily dosing requires intra-day schedule times or multiple dose events per day, which the PRD does not define.",
docs/reviews/user-stories/codex-review.json:1646:    "suggestion": "Expand US-REC-01/02 with the PRD guardrails and add explicit test acceptance criteria for known calculation fixtures."
docs/reviews/user-stories/codex-review.json:1652:    "description": "US-REC-01 says to warn if 'units per dose exceed typical high ranges', which mixes syringe units/volume with dose-range safety. The PRD guardrails distinguish dose range, injection volume, and BAC water volume warnings.",
docs/reviews/user-stories/codex-review.json:1667:    "suggestion": "Expand US-ORD-01 to include vendor configuration, test send behavior, fallback visibility, expired auth code, invalidated session, and vendor-not-found recovery."
docs/reviews/user-stories/codex-review.json:1680:    "description": "US-ORD-05 says inventory is 'automatically updated' when an order is received, while the PRD requires a prompt to add ordered items to inventory and allows reconstitution details to be added later.",
docs/reviews/user-stories/codex-review.json:1695:    "suggestion": "Split US-AUT-01 into Power User and Delegated Participant onboarding paths, with role-specific steps and dismissal/completion behavior."
docs/reviews/user-stories/codex-review.json:1722:    "description": "The sourcing journey labels the inventory alert as US-ORD-02 and the order builder as US-ORD-03, but US-ORD-02 is only inventory-aware suggestions inside the builder, not an alert/notification story.",
